The paper deals with an online matching problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves minimizing the expected total cost of the matching, which suggests that it may also be related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and competitive analysis, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
